		.col-lg-6
			| Fr. Varghese Mattamana is an MBA from Xavier's Institute. He has vast experience in managing several organizations including Caritas India where he served as Executive Director for 10 years. Fr. Varghese is also a senate member of Gandhi Gram Rural Development directly appointed by Vice President of India. Prior to Caritas, father was the Director of Social Services for Kerala Catholic Bishop's Conference. He has closely worked with many educational institutions and helped them reach new heights. He is also actively involved in establishing schools under Malankara Syrian Catholic Church across India. Currently, he is associated with Pune diocese, Maharashtra.
